  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I suggest making `dbutils.ChangeSet` a helper type only used for gathering changes and persisting them to the database (Gather + Encode API). For reading and interpreting the data stored in the database, we need to have the API that works directly on the byte slice `[]byte`, without having to deserialise it into a `ChangeSet`. That means that `ChangeSet` should not have a Decode API (deserialisation). That, in turns removes the necessity to have \"IsSorted\" invariant maintained about the `ChangeSet` and we can remove sorting from the `Add` function. Sorting should be performed just before we write the changeSet into the DB. Also, `MultiAdd` may becomes superfluous, and removed in favour of simply accumulating values in a `ChangeSet`. \r\n",
